# 2p_ctf — host side. Plays the RED team. Uses the Crossfire map's
# auto-spawn (slot 0 → red side after team auto-balance).
#
# Flow:
#   1. Lobby + countdown (~tick 0–130) — auto_start fires.
#   2. ROUND_START — host spawns at red lane, client spawns at blue.
#   3. Host arms a carry of the BLUE flag via the flag_carry debug
#      directive (would otherwise need ~14 sec of running across the
#      whole map). The dirty bit is set; main.c broadcasts FLAG_STATE
#      to the client.
#   4. Host walks LEFT into the RED home flag at (320, 974). The
#      both-flags-home capture rule fires: +5 RED team, BLUE flag
#      sent home. Both flags land HOME again.
#
# The shot test pairs with 2p_ctf.client.shot which is a stationary
# observer that captures the same key moments from the BLUE side. The
# flag pip on the client should pulse during the carry then return to
# solid HOME after the capture.

window 1280 720
out build/shots/net/host_ctf
network host 24017
name HostRed

contact_sheet sheet cols 4 cell 320 180

# Host's local mech spawns naturally on the red platform after
# ROUND_START (~tick 130). Capture pre-round banner.
at 60  shot t60_lobby
at 140 shot t140_round_start
at 180 shot t180_player_settled

# Arm the BLUE-flag carry. Triggers a FLAG_STATE broadcast.
at 200 flag_carry 1
at 215 shot t215_carrying_blue

# Walk RIGHT into the RED home flag at x=320 (~130 px from spawn at 192).
# Capture should fire within ~30 ticks. mech_chest closes on flag.home_pos
# at run speed (~4.6 px/tick).
at 220 press right
at 270 release right
at 280 shot t280_just_after_capture
at 320 shot t320_post_capture_settled

at 700 shot t700_round_end
at 760 end
